Mr. Marcelo (born August 13, 1976) is an American rapper who was briefly signed to No Limit Records in 2000.
Taking his name from New Orleans mobster, Carlos Marcello, Mr. Marcelo released his debut album, Brick Livin' through No Limit Records on July 25, 2000.
He achieved local success in 1992 with a song called "Hey P-Popper", which was a very popular dance at that time.
In 2000 he was featured on the 504 Boyz single "Whodi", and released his first album, Brick Livin', his only hit.
In 2001 he released a second album, Streetz Got Luv 4 Me, which was not successful.
He released a third album, Still Brick Livin' , in 2004 on his own label, Brick Livin Entertainment, and a fourth album, Son of Magnolia, in 2006 on the Ball or Fall Records label.
